,(1768,16,'_content_builder_2_members_0_image','field_team_image'),(1769,16,'content_builder_2_members_0_image_hover','49'),(1770,16,'_content_builder_2_members_0_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(1771,16,'content_builder_2_members_0_first_name','Jennifer'),(1772,16,'_content_builder_2_members_0_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(1773,16,'content_builder_2_members_0_last_name','Penrose'),(1774,16,'_content_builder_2_members_0_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(1775,16,'content_builder_2_members_0_position','DPT, OCS, MTC, Owner'),(1776,16,'_content_builder_2_members_0_position','field_team_position'),(1777,16,'content_builder_2_members_0_email','jennifer@penrosept.com'),(1778,16,'_content_builder_2_members_0_email','field_team_email'),(1779,16,'content_builder_2_members_0_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\">Board Certification in Orthopedics:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>March 2005.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Only 6% of all licensed physical therapists are board certified in orthopedics.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Undergraduate Education:</strong>\r\nNorthwestern College, Orange City, IA\r\nBachelor of Arts, Magna Cum Laude, May 1998\r\nHonors and tennis scholarships</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Physical Therapy School</strong>\r\nEastern Washington University, Spokane, WA\r\nMaster’s in Physical Therapy, Summa Cum Laude, Dec. 2000\r\nCASE scholarship, AMBUCS scholarship, &amp; John Joy scholarship</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Post-graduate Doctorate</strong>\r\nTransitional Doctorate of Physical Therapy\r\nUniversity of St. Augustine, FL April 2006</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Publication:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Hennington G, Johnson J, Penrose J, Barr K, McMulkin ML, Vander Linden DW.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Effect of bench height on sit to stand in children with disabilities and children with cerebral palsy.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Arch Phys Med Rehabil.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>2004: Jan;85(1):70-6.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Shoulder rehabilitation:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>impingement/bursitis, rotator cuff tendonitis &amp; repairs, shoulder instabilities, and shoulder osteoarthritis. In conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Trent McKay, MD March 2008.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Total knee replacement rehabilitation:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Anthony Agtarap, MD November 2007.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Spinal Instabilities:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Non-surgical treatment.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Presented at Sports Medicine Conference to primary care providers in conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Chris Peterson, DO April 2006.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Ankle sprains and chronic ankle instability:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Presented at Sports Medicine Conference to primary care providers in conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Steve Snow, MD May 2004.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Tennis injuries:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>rehabilitation and prevention.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Thomas Helpenstell, MD in 2003 and then again in 2004 with orthopedic surgeon Steve Snow, MD.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Get informed about osteoporosis, risk of falls, and osteoarthritis.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Presented at the YMCA 2004.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Traumatic Shoulder Dislocations:</strong> non-operative management, rotator cuff rehabilitation.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Presented at Sports Medicine conference to primary care providers in conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Chris Peterson, DO 2003.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Bio: Dr.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Jennifer Penrose enjoys working with a variety of sports and orthopedic injuries.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Her manual therapy certification (MTC) provides her with the hands on skills needed to mobilize joints and soft tissues.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“I love working with my hands to increase patient’s mobility and decrease their pain.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She also enjoys looking at how patients move in order to determine what dysfunctional movement pattern may be causing their pain.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“We are movement analysts or mechanics with the human body.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She also enjoys teaching patients and the public about their pain/injury, what the possible causes are, and how to rehabilitate the injury.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“Patients have less fear and anxiety and less pain about their injury when we explain the normal process of healing and pain and what to expect along this rehabilitation journey.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We want to make this a comfortable, learning, and successful process.”</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Dr. Penrose’s reputation and expertise has gained her a broad base of referral relationships with various health providers, specifically in orthopedics, internal medicine, family practice, and podiatry. She has co-lectured with local surgeons Dr. Agtarap, Dr. Helpenstell, Dr. McKay, and Dr. Snow to the public on various rehabilitation issues such as knees, ankles, shoulders, and spine.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She has also lectured at sports medicine conferences to primary care providers on various topics.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In addition to lending her musculoskeletal expertise to health practitioners, she has presented to different community organizations on the progression of osteoporosis and sports injury prevention. She also enjoys working with the running population evaluating running mechanics and continues to run half marathons herself and give running workshops to the public.</p>'),(1780,16,'_content_builder_2_members_0_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(1781,16,'content_builder_2_members_0_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Power of One</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Choosing to See</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why I live in the South Sound:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Mountains, ocean, close to Seattle and Portland.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Sports Moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>When my 8 year old son qualified &amp; participated in the USATF Junior Olympic Cross Country National Championships.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst Injury ever suffered:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>13mm disc herniation at L5-S1 that could not be rehabilitated resulting in a micro-discectomy surgery.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When you are not at work:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>With my 3 boys and spouse, running, traveling, on the beach in the sun, eating great food, or shopping.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best Advice:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>You can only control 2 things in life:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Attitude and Effort.</p>'),(1782,16,'_content_builder_2_members_0_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(1783,16,'content_builder_2_members_1_image','23'),(1784,16,'_content_builder_2_members_1_image','field_team_image'),(1785,16,'content_builder_2_members_1_image_hover','48'),(1786,16,'_content_builder_2_members_1_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(1787,16,'content_builder_2_members_1_first_name','Chris'),(1788,16,'_content_builder_2_members_1_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(1789,16,'content_builder_2_members_1_last_name','Edwards'),(1790,16,'_content_builder_2_members_1_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(1791,16,'content_builder_2_members_1_position','PTA'),(1792,16,'_content_builder_2_members_1_position','field_team_position'),(1793,16,'content_builder_2_members_1_email','chris@penrosept.com'),(1794,16,'_content_builder_2_members_1_email','field_team_email'),(1795,16,'content_builder_2_members_1_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\">Chris Edwards is a Licensed Physical Therapist Assistant.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He assists the physical therapists in treating their patients.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>They are a team that communicates regularly regarding each patient’s status and progress.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He is an expert at challenging patients with progressive exercises without increasing pain.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“I enjoy finding new ways to work muscles that patients find challenging and at the same time applicable to their goals.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He has training in Graston technique and kinesiotaping.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He is also certified in functional range conditioning.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He has been a vital piece to the success &amp; team at Penrose Physical Therapy.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He truly loves to learn the latest evidence and techniques in physical therapy which benefits the patients and our practice.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">As a child Chris grew up north of Seattle but moved to Kansas with his family when he was 12, where he would later meet his beautiful wife and they would begin raising their five children.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He became a PTA in Kansas where he graduated with Honors as member of the Phi Theta Kappa with multiple Academic awards including top two in his class to pass state boards.</p>'),(1796,16,'_content_builder_2_members_1_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(1797,16,'content_builder_2_members_1_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>The Family Man</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>I confess I read mostly physical therapy articles and research latest treatment techniques.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I also love to read about new recipes.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I love great food!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why you live in the South Sound/WA:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>I grew up here and knew at some point I would return with my family.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Sports Moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>The Seahawks first Superbowl win in 2014 of course!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst Injury you have suffered:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>A broken wrist playing basket-ball when I was 16 with my arm casted all the way to my shoulder.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">When you are not at work you are:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Enjoying time with my 5 kids and amazing spouse!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Watching the Seahawks!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Cooking.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best advice you ever got:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>The kind of person you are is not defined by the choices you’ve made and your future is not determined by your past.</p>'),(1798,16,'_content_builder_2_members_1_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(1799,16,'content_builder_2_members_2_image','41'),(1800,16,'_content_builder_2_members_2_image','field_team_image'),(1801,16,'content_builder_2_members_2_image_hover','56'),(1802,16,'_content_builder_2_members_2_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(1803,16,'content_builder_2_members_2_first_name','Stephanie'),(1804,16,'_content_builder_2_members_2_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(1805,16,'content_builder_2_members_2_last_name','Gibson'),(1806,16,'_content_builder_2_members_2_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(1807,16,'content_builder_2_members_2_position','Part time Physical Therapy Aide and Front Office'),(1808,16,'_content_builder_2_members_2_position','field_team_position'),(1809,16,'content_builder_2_members_2_email','stephanie@penrosept.com'),(1810,16,'_content_builder_2_members_2_email','field_team_email'),(1811,16,'content_builder_2_members_2_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\">Stephanie enjoys helping people and empowering them to help others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“I enjoy watching patients succeed and find joy in being part of a team that works so hard to benefit others.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She grew up in Texas where she graduated with a Bachelors Degree in Social Work.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Her social work degree and experience in working with a refugee agency and church planting provides a unique compassionate service oriented approach at Penrose Physical Therapy.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In her spare time she likes being with friends, reading, painting, running, and biking.</p>'),(1812,16,'_content_builder_2_members_2_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(1813,16,'content_builder_2_members_2_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:</strong> How to lose a guy in 10 days</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>The Giver</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why you live in the South Sound/WA:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Came to help a church plant but in the process fell in love with the beauty of WA and the abundance of delicious coffee!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Sports Moment:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Sportsmanship displayed at the softball game between CWU and WOU in 2008.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>An outfielder from WOU hit her first ever home run and injured her knee rounding first.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>2 players from CWU carried her around the bases to complete her home run.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst Injury you have suffered:</strong> Having a toe nail ripped off when moving a couch over it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When you are not at work you are:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Movies/games with friends, reading, running, drinking coffee.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best advice you ever got:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>If you’re not going to do anything about it then stop complaining.</p>'),(1814,16,'_content_builder_2_members_2_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(1815,16,'content_builder_2_members_3_image','34'),(1816,16,'_content_builder_2_members_3_image','field_team_image'),(1817,16,'content_builder_2_members_3_image_hover','52'),(1818,16,'_content_builder_2_members_3_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(1819,16,'content_builder_2_members_3_first_name','Kristin'),(1820,16,'_content_builder_2_members_3_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(1821,16,'content_builder_2_members_3_last_name','Olson'),(1822,16,'_content_builder_2_members_3_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(1823,16,'content_builder_2_members_3_position','Part time Physical Therapy Aide and Front Office'),(1824,16,'_content_builder_2_members_3_position','field_team_position'),(1825,16,'content_builder_2_members_3_email','Kristin@penrosept.com'),(1826,16,'_content_builder_2_members_3_email','field_team_email'),(1827,16,'content_builder_2_members_3_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\">Kristin has 6 years of experience in the customer service field and strides to provide excellent patient experiences at Penrose Physical Therapy. “I want to make sure each patient has a positive experience even though they are in pain.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Kristin assists the therapists with patient care and has continued her education in physical therapy assistant school. <span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She will graduate in the spring of 2017 with her PTA degree.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We are proud to have mentored her in that journey.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In her spare time Kristin enjoys soccer and spending time outdoors fishing, hiking, snowboarding, and maintaining a healthy lifestyle.</p>'),(1828,16,'_content_builder_2_members_3_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(1829,16,'content_builder_2_members_3_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Where the heart is</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Because of Winn Dixie</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why you live in the South Sound/WA:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Because of its beauty of course!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Sports Moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Winning powderpuff football in high-school against the seniors!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst Injury you have suffered:</strong> A dog bite</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When you are not at work you are:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Currently studying to finish PTA school!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Otherwise outdoors fishing, hiking, snowboard enjoying the Pacific Northwest!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best advice you ever got:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>It is a good day to have a good day!</p>'),(1830,16,'_content_builder_2_members_3_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(1831,16,'content_builder_2_members_4_image','38'),(1832,16,'_content_builder_2_members_4_image','field_team_image'),(1833,16,'content_builder_2_members_4_image_hover','54'),(1834,16,'_content_builder_2_members_4_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(1835,16,'content_builder_2_members_4_first_name','Ryan'),(1836,16,'_content_builder_2_members_4_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(1837,16,'content_builder_2_members_4_last_name','Critser'),(1838,16,'_content_builder_2_members_4_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(1839,16,'content_builder_2_members_4_position','(LMP) Licensed Massage Practitioner'),(1840,16,'_content_builder_2_members_4_position','field_team_position'),(1841,16,'content_builder_2_members_4_email','dreaandryanc@gmail.com'),(1842,16,'_content_builder_2_members_4_email','field_team_email'),(1843,16,'content_builder_2_members_4_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\">Ryan graduated from Brenneke School of Massage in 2002. He has considerable experience working with injured clients in clinical settings such as chiropractic and at Penrose PT.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He provides a safe environment where he listens to his client\'s goals and concerns. Comfort levels are taken into consideration for all ranges, from first time clients to long time veterans. “Each client is different in their expectation and tolerance for massage therapy; I listen to them and adjust the massage according to what they need and tolerate.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Ryan is trained in a variety of techniques including: treatment of various orthopedic injuries, sport related injuries, nationally certified in pregnancy massage, myofascial deep tissue, trigger point, and relaxing Swedish massage. Ryan also uses moist hot packs to ensure client\'s maximum comfort during the massage process.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Ryan is a big family man! He has been married to his wife for eight amazing years and is a father to a fantastic seven year old daughter.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">**Ryan accepts a majority of all insurance plans including Regence. He is available at Penrose Physical Therapy on Tuesdays. Cash Clients: 1 hour massage - $60.00; 30 minute massage - $35.00</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Cell: </b>360-584-6086 as he manages his own schedule for clients</p>'),(1844,16,'_content_builder_2_members_4_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(1845,16,'content_builder_2_members_4_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Goonies</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Where the wild things are (yes it is a children’s book but it’s an escape for me!)</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why you live in the South Sound/WA:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Born in WA and raised by a single mom!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We made it work as a team!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Sports Moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>When Richard Sherman blocked Crabtree’s pass in the end zone during a playoff game.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst Injury you have suffered:</strong> Broken left collar bone in 5<sup>th</sup> grade.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">When you are not at work you are:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Working or studying.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I prefer to be with my amazing wife and daughter!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“I’m a family man and a workaholic!”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">   </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Best advice you ever got:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Be bold and mighty forces will come to your aid.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>May the force be with you.</p>'),(1846,16,'_content_builder_2_members_4_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(1847,16,'content_builder_2_members_5_image','44'),(1848,16,'_content_builder_2_members_5_image','field_team_image'),(1849,16,'content_builder_2_members_5_image_hover','45'),(1850,16,'_content_builder_2_members_5_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(1851,16,'content_builder_2_members_5_first_name','Andrew'),(1852,16,'_content_builder_2_members_5_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(1853,16,'content_builder_2_members_5_last_name','Blagg'),(1854,16,'_content_builder_2_members_5_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(1855,16,'content_builder_2_members_5_position','Clinical Exercise Physiologist'),(1856,16,'_content_builder_2_members_5_position','field_team_position'),(1857,16,'content_builder_2_members_5_email','fds@gmail.com'),(1858,16,'_content_builder_2_members_5_email','field_team_email'),(1859,16,'content_builder_2_members_5_professional_bio','Based on my research and experience, I am convinced that exercise is an extremely powerful measure for preventing the development of health conditions such as musculoskeletal dysfunction (e.g. low-back pain, arthritis), obesity, diabetes, heart disease and osteoporosis. Exercise is also a very effective post-rehabilitative therapy.'),(1860,16,'_content_builder_2_members_5_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(1861,16,'content_builder_2_members_5_personal_bio','It would be my pleasure to help you with a safe and effective exercise program. If you are interested, please call (206) 476-2698 or email andyblagg@yahoo.com for a free consultation.\r\n<table border=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Training Hours</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Monday</td>\r\n<td>5:30pm - 7:00pm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tuesday</td>\r\n<td>4:00pm - 7:00pm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Thursday</td>\r\n<td>4:00pm - 7:00pm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Friday</td>\r\n<td>5:30pm - 7:00pm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Saturday</td>\r\n<td>8:00am - 12:00pm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>'),(1862,16,'_content_builder_2_members_5_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(1863,16,'content_builder_2_members_6_image','36'),(1864,16,'_content_builder_2_members_6_image','field_team_image'),(1865,16,'content_builder_2_members_6_image_hover','53'),(1866,16,'_content_builder_2_members_6_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(1867,16,'content_builder_2_members_6_first_name','Lerae'),(1868,16,'_content_builder_2_members_6_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(1869,16,'content_builder_2_members_6_last_name','Ketchum'),(1870,16,'_content_builder_2_members_6_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(1871,16,'content_builder_2_members_6_position','Administrative Assistant'),(1872,16,'_content_builder_2_members_6_position','field_team_position'),(1873,16,'content_builder_2_members_6_email','lerae@penrosept.com'),(1874,16,'_content_builder_2_members_6_email','field_team_email'),(1875,16,'content_builder_2_members_6_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\">Lerae graduated from local Timberline High School &amp; will continue her education in Art Therapy.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Along with being on the Honor Roll all four years of high school, she played volleyball for multiple teams and assisted in coaching a co-ed softball team.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Lerae embodies the culture at Penrose Physical Therapy.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She loves to help others and wants to bring a smile to each person she meets.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She has volunteered with many different groups, Rotary, assisting with care taking, and many church functions.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In working at Penrose &amp; Associates Lerae greets everyone warmly and hopes to be an encouragement to them from the moment they enter the front door.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She understands her role on the team in assisting patients at check and with assisting the therapist with patient care.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In her spare time Lerae loves to spend time outdoors with her family and loving dog and anything dealing with art!</p>'),(1876,16,'_content_builder_2_members_6_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(1877,16,'content_builder_2_members_6_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Seven Pounds</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>1984 by George Orwell</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why you live in the South Sound:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Grew up here and can’t imagine being far away from family!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite sports moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>In middle school I was finally able to get my serve over the net (7’ 12”)!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst injury suffered:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>At circuit city my mom told me to sit down on a shelving unit and the whole thing fell down fracturing my leg and ankle.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When you are not at work:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>At the gym or enjoying time with my family and my dog.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best Advice you ever got:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Don’t stress about what you cannot change, but put your energy into what you can and God will take care of the rest.</p>'),(1878,16,'_content_builder_2_members_6_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(1879,16,'content_builder_2_members_7_image','57'),(1880,16,'_content_builder_2_members_7_image','field_team_image'),(1881,16,'content_builder_2_members_7_image_hover','57'),(1882,16,'_content_builder_2_members_7_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(1883,16,'content_builder_2_members_7_first_name','Trina'),(1884,16,'_content_builder_2_members_7_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(1885,16,'content_builder_2_members_7_last_name','LASTNAME'),(1886,16,'_content_builder_2_members_7_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(1887,16,'content_builder_2_members_7_position','Accounting'),(1888,16,'_content_builder_2_members_7_position','field_team_position'),(1889,16,'content_builder_2_members_7_email','foo@bar.com'),(1890,16,'_content_builder_2_members_7_email','field_team_email'),(1891,16,'content_builder_2_members_7_professional_bio','Progressive Billing Specialists has been doing Physical Therapy billing for 16 years. Trina Fykerud, owner of Progressive Billing Specialists, received her BS degree in Business Administration from WWU in 1991, with a concentration in Human Resource Management and Entrepreneurial Business. Prior to starting her business, Trina worked for St. Joseph Home Health Care as a Reimbursement Specialist. She worked directly with case managers to get approval for home care and met with patients at the UW Hospital to help them understand their insurance benefits prior to being discharged. Trina also spent a few years as a certified personal trainer and nutrition consultant. She can be reached by phone at <strong>360-863-6923</strong> or by email at <strong>trina@progressivebillingspecialists.com</strong>'),(1892,16,'_content_builder_2_members_7_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(1893,16,'content_builder_2_members_7_personal_bio','Progressive Billing Specialists has been doing Physical Therapy billing for 16 years. Trina Fykerud, owner of Progressive Billing Specialists, received her BS degree in Business Administration from WWU in 1991, with a concentration in Human Resource Management and Entrepreneurial Business. Prior to starting her business, Trina worked for St. Joseph Home Health Care as a Reimbursement Specialist. She worked directly with case managers to get approval for home care and met with patients at the UW Hospital to help them understand their insurance benefits prior to being discharged. Trina also spent a few years as a certified personal trainer and nutrition consultant. She can be reached by phone at <strong>360-863-6923</strong> or by email at <strong>trina@progressivebillingspecialists.com</strong>'),(1894,16,'_content_builder_2_members_7_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(1895,16,'content_builder_2_members_8_image','50'),(1896,16,'_content_builder_2_members_8_image','field_team_image'),(1897,16,'content_builder_2_members_8_image_hover','51'),(1898,16,'_content_builder_2_members_8_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(1899,16,'content_builder_2_members_8_first_name','Kristen'),(1900,16,'_content_builder_2_members_8_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(1901,16,'content_builder_2_members_8_last_name','Weaver'),(1902,16,'_content_builder_2_members_8_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(1903,16,'content_builder_2_members_8_position','MSPT, Cert MDT, CMPT, Part Time Staff Physical Therapist'),(1904,16,'_content_builder_2_members_8_position','field_team_position'),(1905,16,'content_builder_2_members_8_email','info@penrosept.com'),(1906,16,'_content_builder_2_members_8_email','field_team_email'),(1907,16,'content_builder_2_members_8_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><b>Grand Valley State University </b>Allendale, MI</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Master of Science in Physical Therapy Spring 2004</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Bachelor of Science in Health Sciences Spring 2002</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Special Certifications\r\n</b>Certified Manual Therapist (NAIOMT) August 2013</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">McKenzie Certified Therapist October 2006</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Kristen has been a PT since 2004 and has quite a variety of experiences from home health, skilled nursing, to primarily outpatient orthopedics.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She has found that orthopedics has a nice variety with working with her hands and the neuromuscular system as a whole.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“I have an interest in manual therapy and exercise to re-train the neural connections between the brain and muscles to gain optimal function.”  She is committed to finding the root cause(s) to a patient’s pain or mobility problem.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“It is important to me to discover the specific impairments a patient may have and then develop an individualized treatment plan that is practical and fun!”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We are excited to have her on the team.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Kristen works part time so she can balance life with her 3 kids!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She enjoys the outdoors and time with her husband.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Zumba is also a fun activity that allows her to keep up with her active kids.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She also enjoys quiet time studying the Bible and volunteering for MOPS (Mothers of Preschoolers).</p>'),(1908,16,'_content_builder_2_members_8_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(1909,16,'content_builder_2_members_8_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Inspirational movies like “The Prayer Room”</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Inspirational books like Karen Kingsbury books and Ted Dekker books</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why you live in the South Sound/WA:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>I love the variety of landscape/nature.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I love the mountains, the lakes, the rivers, rainforest, the ocean.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Sports Moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>I loved competing in rock climbing competitions with friends in college.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst Injury you have suffered:</strong> Childbirth!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>It was quite a recovery process each time.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When you are not at work you are:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Enjoying time with my 3 young kids and spouse! <span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I may also be out camping, hiking, water and snow skiing, rock climbing, mountain biking, gardening, and creating adventures.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best advice you ever got:</strong> Love your husband by showing that you respect him.</p>'),(1910,16,'_content_builder_2_members_8_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(1911,16,'content_builder_2_members_9_image','46'),(1912,16,'_content_builder_2_members_9_image','field_team_image'),(1913,16,'content_builder_2_members_9_image_hover','47'),(1914,16,'_content_builder_2_members_9_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(1915,16,'content_builder_2_members_9_first_name','Catie'),(1916,16,'_content_builder_2_members_9_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(1917,16,'content_builder_2_members_9_last_name','Lynn'),(1918,16,'_content_builder_2_members_9_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(1919,16,'content_builder_2_members_9_position','Part time Physical Therapy Aide and Front Office'),(1920,16,'_content_builder_2_members_9_position','field_team_position'),(1921,16,'content_builder_2_members_9_email','catie@penrosept.com'),(1922,16,'_content_builder_2_members_9_email','field_team_email'),(1923,16,'content_builder_2_members_9_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\">Catie joins our team after graduating high-school 1 year early.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She enjoys helping and serving others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She is exploring what schooling or career she will do next.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“I am honored to be part of a team that enjoys what they do and part of something where you can see people get better at each visit.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Her compassion and willingness to serve is a joy to have as we mentor her along in the journey of what life has for her next steps.</p>'),(1924,16,'_content_builder_2_members_9_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(1925,16,'content_builder_2_members_9_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Original Ben Hur</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Les Miserables</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why you live in the South Sound/WA:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Currently living with extended family in WA.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I am grateful to live and work in healthy/supportive environments to help determine the next steps in my life for school or career.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Sports Moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>When my little sister scored her first points in a basketball game.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She was so thrilled.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The joy watching her was so fun.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst Injury you have suffered:</strong> When I accidentally cut open one of the tendons in my hand.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When you are not at work you are:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Reading, writing/journaling, or talking with family.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best advice you ever got:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>It’s impossible to please everyone, but don’t worry about it you’re not responsible for other people’s feelings.</p>'),(1926,16,'_content_builder_2_members_9_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(1927,16,'content_builder_2_members','10'),(1928,16,'_content_builder_2_members','field_members'),(1933,16,'content_builder_3_drop_caps_letter','T'),(1934,16,'_content_builder_3_drop_caps_letter','field_drop_caps_let