nce: \"I eventually ended up at Penrose and they fixed the problem within a couple of weeks.\"'),(2121,18,'content_builder_0_image','204'),(2122,18,'_content_builder_0_image','field_right_image'),(2123,18,'content_builder_1_content','&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5>Chronic Pain</h5>\r\nDue to advances in neuroscience, we now know that we can treat <em>chronic pain</em> from a neurological approach. We use what is called <strong>Graded Motor Imagery or \"GMI\" </strong>and<strong> Mirror Therapy.  </strong>We will treat your pain and educate you on how you can finally begin to control it neurologically and physiologically.\r\n\r\nThis condition can be very debilitating and depressing, therefore, we take the time to listen to you. We will communicate with other health professionals as needed to help you increase your function.'),(2124,18,'_content_builder_1_content','field_right_content'),(2125,18,'content_builder_1_video_heading','\"Why Things Hurt\" Lorimer Moseley'),(2126,18,'_content_builder_1_video_heading','field_service_video_heading'),(2127,18,'content_builder_1_video','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gwd-wLdIHjs'),(2128,18,'_content_builder_1_video','field_service_video'),(2129,18,'content_builder_1_video_image','192'),(2130,18,'_content_builder_1_video_image','field_service_video_image'),(2131,18,'content_builder_2_heading','Why choose us?'),(2132,18,'_content_builder_2_heading','field_comparison_heading'),(2133,18,'content_builder_2_comparison_table_0_comparison_text','Treatment'),(2134,18,'_content_builder_2_comparison_table_0_comparison_text','field_comparison_text'),(2135,18,'content_builder_2_comparison_table_0_typical_text','Clearly explaining what is causing your pain?  Did you have a thorough orthopedic examination with a definite diagnosis?'),(2136,18,'_content_builder_2_comparison_table_0_typical_text','field_comparison_typical'),(2137,18,'content_builder_2_comparison_table_1_comparison_text','Resources & Support'),(2138,18,'_content_builder_2_comparison_table_1_comparison_text','field_comparison_text'),(2139,18,'content_builder_2_comparison_table_1_typical_text','Providing practical, immediate methods to reduce your discomfort?'),(2140,18,'_content_builder_2_comparison_table_1_typical_text','field_comparison_typical'),(2141,18,'content_builder_2_comparison_table_2_comparison_text','Cost'),(2142,18,'_content_builder_2_comparison_table_2_comparison_text','field_comparison_text'),(2143,18,'content_builder_2_comparison_table_2_typical_text','Checking your insurance coverage ahead of time and explain your out of pocket expense?  Do they work with you on treatment frequency?'),(2144,18,'_content_builder_2_comparison_table_2_typical_text','field_comparison_typical'),(2145,18,'content_builder_2_comparison_table_3_comparison_text','Team'),(2146,18,'_content_builder_2_comparison_table_3_comparison_text','field_comparison_text'),(2147,18,'content_builder_2_comparison_table_3_typical_text','Friendly and happy to assist you with your questions?'),(2148,18,'_content_builder_2_comparison_table_3_typical_text','field_comparison_typical'),(2149,18,'content_builder_2_comparison_table','4'),(2150,18,'_content_builder_2_comparison_table','field_comparison_table'),(2151,18,'content_builder_3_cases_0_case','120'),(2152,18,'_content_builder_3_cases_0_case','field_case'),(2153,18,'content_builder_3_cases_1_case','213'),(2154,18,'_content_builder_3_cases_1_case','field_case'),(2155,18,'content_builder_3_cases','2'),(2156,18,'_content_builder_3_cases','field_cases'),(2157,18,'content_builder_1_image','288'),(2158,18,'_content_builder_1_image','field_left_image'),(2159,18,'content_builder_2_content','Acute pain is unpleasant and we are committed to using a variety of techniques to decrease your pain.  The musculoskeletal system is designed to move.   The joints, tendons, &amp; muscles love range of motion.  “Motion is Lotion.”  However, with pain sometimes you need guidance on how to move and what motions will work that do not increase pain.  We will use hands on techniques and often times modalities like ultrasound, electrical stimulation, kinesiotaping to assist in decreasing your pain.\r\n\r\nChronic Pain:  At Penrose Physical Therapy we understand that pain is individual and it is real.  We also know with the advances in neuroscience that the brain can start to have changes in the neuromatrix if pain becomes chronic.  Due to the recent advances in neuroscience we now know we can treat chronic pain from a neurological approach using what is called <strong>“Graded Motor Imagery\" or GMI and Mirror Therapy</strong> when indicated.  We are committed to treating your pain and educating you on how you can begin to control your pain physiologically and neurologically.\r\n\r\nPain can be very debilitating and depressing.  We take the time to communicate with other health professionals to help decrease your pain and increase your function.'),(2160,18,'_content_builder_2_content','field_service_content'),(2161,18,'content_builder_2_video_heading','\"Why Things Hurt\" Lorimer Moseley'),(2162,18,'_content_builder_2_video_heading','field_service_video_heading'),(2163,18,'content_builder_2_video','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gwd-wLdIHjs'),(2164,18,'_content_builder_2_video','field_service_video'),(2165,18,'content_builder_2_video_image','192'),(2166,18,'_content_builder_2_video_image','field_service_video_image'),(2207,76,'_yoast_wpseo_focuskw_text_input','osteoporosis'),(2208,76,'_yoast_wpseo_focuskw','osteoporosis'),(2209,76,'_yoast_wpseo_linkdex','81'),(2210,11,'_wp_old_slug','story-1'),(2211,11,'_yoast_wpseo_focuskw_text_input','tendonitis'),(2212,11,'_yoast_wpseo_focuskw','tendonitis'),(2213,11,'_yoast_wpseo_linkdex','74'),(2238,210,'_edit_lock','1487891813:4'),(2239,210,'_edit_last','2'),(2240,210,'_thumbnail_id','412'),(2241,210,'content_builder_0_content','Alisha fell down the stairs causing a complicated fracture and multiple sprains in her foot and ankle.  Her ankle/foot surgeon told her she may end up needing surgery but to try physical therapy first.  Dr.  Michael Dujela, DPM wanted to give her body the chance to rehabilitate without surgery first.  After 2 months of walking in a boot she arrived at Penrose Physical Therapy with significant pain, very limited mobility in her ankle and foot, significant swelling, walking with a limp, and she was very skeptical that physical therapy would be able to help.'),(2242,210,'_content_builder_0_content','field_service_content'),(2243,210,'content_builder_0_image','283'),(2244,210,'_content_builder_0_image','field_right_image'),(2245,210,'content_builder_1_content','<h1>Solution</h1>\r\nPenrose Physical Therapy used manual therapy techniques to mobilize the ankle and foot joints to allow for more range of motion.  Graded progressive exercises for motion and strength were given that she could do at work and at home.  As more range of motion was achieved, walking and balance exercises were started.'),(2246,210,'_content_builder_1_content','field_center_content'),(2247,210,'content_builder_2_image','289'),(2248,210,'_content_builder_2_image','field_left_image'),(2249,210,'content_builder_2_content','<h1>Result</h1>\r\nAfter 4 months working with Penrose Physical Therapy Alisha has near full range of motion and is able to walk a mile without limping.  She is returning to the gym and gradually increasing her activity levels without increased pain.  Her surgeon thought it would have taken her closer to 12 months to be at this level of function.  Her surgeon, Dr.  Michael Dujela, DPM, no longer thinks surgery will be needed.'),(2250,210,'_content_builder_2_content','field_right_content'),(2251,210,'content_builder','a:3:{i:0;s:7:\"service\";i:1;s:14:\"center_content\";i:2;s:13:\"right_content\";}'),(2252,210,'_content_builder','field_builder'),(2253,210,'header_heading',''),(2254,210,'_header_heading','field_heading'),(2255,210,'header_background','173'),(2256,210,'_header_background','field_background'),(2257,210,'testimonial_author','Alisha Miller '),(2258,210,'_testimonial_author','field_testimonial_author'),(2259,210,'testimonial_content','I felt heard.  I felt like there was a lot of creativity...I actually looked forward to coming.'),(2260,210,'_testimonial_content','field_testimonial_content'),(2261,210,'testimonial_logo','108'),(2262,210,'_testimonial_logo','field_testimonial_logo'),(2263,210,'_yoast_wpseo_content_score','30'),(2264,211,'_edit_lock','1487891833:4'),(2265,211,'_edit_last','2'),(2266,211,'_thumbnail_id','336'),(2267,211,'content_builder_0_content','<h1>Challenge</h1>\r\nMark started physical therapy a week after a rotator cuff and labral repair shoulder surgery with a 73% disability score from the standardized “Shoulder Pain and Disability Index.”  He was not allowed to move his arm in the beginning and wore a sling.  He was looking at not being able to actively raise his arm for 6 weeks and restoring full range of motion and strength would take several months.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-235\" src=\"https://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Injuryrehab2-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-275\" src=\"https://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Handsonexercise-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" />'),(2268,211,'_content_builder_0_content','field_left_content'),(2269,211,'content_builder_0_image','277'),(2270,211,'_content_builder_0_image','field_right_image'),(2271,211,'content_builder_1_content','<h1>Solution</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe reviewed Mark’s surgical report.  We started him on passive range of motion where the shoulder is relaxed and there is no strain provided on the repaired tissues.  He was gradually progressed with exercises, range of motion, and strength as his healing and surgical protocol allowed.  We provided manual therapy to decrease pain and allow for the scar tissue to be more mobile and less painful and less restrictive.  We tracked his range of motion measurements to ensure progress and delivered them to the surgeon timely.  He was provided home exercises with print outs, explanations, and continual guidance on his healing timeline and what he was allowed to do and when.'),(2272,211,'_content_builder_1_content','field_center_content'),(2273,211,'content_builder_2_image','282'),(2274,211,'_content_builder_2_image','field_left_image'),(2275,211,'content_builder_2_content','<h1>Result</h1>\r\nAfter several months of physical therapy Mark did reach 0% shoulder disability according to the Shoulder Pain and Disability Index.  He achieved full range of motion and full strength and is now pursuing a career in physical therapy.'),(2276,211,'_content_builder_2_content','field_right_content'),(2277,211,'content_builder','a:3:{i:0;s:12:\"left_content\";i:1;s:14:\"center_content\";i:2;s:13:\"right_content\";}'),(2278,211,'_content_builder','field_builder'),(2279,211,'header_heading',''),(2280,211,'_header_heading','field_heading'),(2281,211,'header_background','177'),(2282,211,'_header_background','field_background'),(2283,211,'testimonial_author','Mark Rosales'),(2284,211,'_testimonial_author','field_testimonial_author'),(2285,211,'testimonial_content','During my recovery from a shoulder rotator cuff repair, I experienced the value of an incredible physical therapy team. When Dr. Penrose mapped out the plan, inclusion of manual therapy (a form of massage) was instrumental in pain management, regaining motion, and rebuilding strength.  Surgery is a vulnerable time, and I found Jennifer’s team - from office staff, to the physical therapy assistant and aids - to be outstanding, helpful, and friendly. The experience has inspired me to explore a career in the field. I would recommend this practice for any physical therapy, from post surgery to everyday movement and pain relief.'),(2286,211,'_testimonial_content','field_testimonial_content'),(2287,211,'testimonial_logo','108'),(2288,211,'_testimonial_logo','field_testimonial_logo'),(2289,211,'_yoast_wpseo_content_score','30'),(2290,211,'content_builder_3_content','<h2>In Mark\'s Own Words</h2>\r\n“During my recovery from a shoulder rotator cuff repair, I experienced the value of an incredible physical therapy team. When Dr. Penrose mapped out the plan, inclusion of manual therapy (a form of massage) was instrumental in pain management, regaining motion, and rebuilding strength.  Surgery is a vulnerable time, and I found Jennifer’s team - from office staff, to the physical therapy assistant and aids - to be outstanding, helpful, and friendly. The experience has inspired me to explore a career in the field. I would recommend this practice for any physical therapy, from post surgery to everyday movement and pain relief.”'),(2291,211,'_content_builder_3_content','field_center_content'),(2293,120,'content_builder_3_content','<h2>In Her Own Words</h2>\r\n“I came back to Jennifer Penrose because she is methodical in her approach with treating my complex feet/tendons and works with me to find practical solutions.  She truly listens to you.  The staff here is wonderful too.”'),(2294,120,'_content_builder_3_content','field_center_content'),(2295,11,'content_builder_3_content','<h1>In Her Own Words</h1>\r\n\"I hurt my foot over a year ago. After several cortisone shots that didn\'t work and 8 months of being in pain I went to a foot and ankle specialist. That didn\'t help either.  I eventually ended up at Penrose and within a couple weeks they have fixed a problem that has been going on for the last year.\"'),(2296,11,'_content_builder_3_content','field_center_content'),(2297,213,'_edit_lock','1487892116:4'),(2298,213,'_edit_last','2'),(2299,213,'content_builder_0_content','<h1>Challenge</h1>\r\nTiffany came to physical therapy with a severe case of tennis elbow or lateral epicondylitis.  She had constant pain and was finding waitressing very difficult with constant elbow pain.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>Solution</h1>\r\nManual therapy techniques combined with Kinesiotaping allowed her to move and work with less pain.  She was also given stretches and gradual strengthening exercises.  The kinesiotaping was critical in allowing her to work with less pain.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>Result</h1>\r\nIn 6 visits she was pain free with work and daily life activities.  She had the tools to continue increasing her strength gradually.  She knew that the tendon would need gradual strengthening on her own over the next 6 months.'),(2300,213,'_content_builder_0_content','field_left_content'),(2301,213,'content_builder_0_image','240'),(2302,213,'_content_builder_0_image','field_right_image'),(2303,213,'content_builder_1_content','<h1>Challenge</h1>\r\nJessi came to physical therapy with a severe case of tendonitis in both shoulders.  She had been increasing her participation in cross fit competitions with weight lifting.  Jessi also worked stocking shelves so her shoulders never have a chance to rest.\r\n<h1>Solution</h1>\r\nManual therapy techniques, Graston Technique, and especially the kinesiotaping was critical in allowing her to work with less pain.  Jessi needed more range of motion in her shoulders in order to raise her arms up without pinching on the rotator cuff and biceps tendons.  She learned exercises for stretching and strengthening her rotator cuff and shoulder blade muscles.\r\n<h1>Result</h1>\r\nIn 10 visits she was nearly pain free with work and daily life activities.  She had the tools to continue increasing her strength gradually.  She knew that the tendon would need gradual strengthening on her own over the next 6 months.'),(2304,213,'_content_builder_1_content','field_center_content'),(2309,213,'content_builder','a:2:{i:0;s:12:\"left_content\";i:1;s:14:\"center_content\";}'),(2310,213,'_content_builder','field_builder'),(2311,213,'header_heading',''),(2312,213,'_header_heading','field_heading'),(2313,213,'header_background','274'),(2314,213,'_header_background','field_background'),(2315,213,'testimonial_author','Jessi Arnold-Johnson'),(2316,213,'_testimonial_author','field_testimonial_author'),(2317,213,'testimonial_content','The best place to get PT! Not only do they help you there, they also show you how to you can help yourself with at home exercise. I was feeling better in a span of a few weeks. Everyone there is really nice and knowledgeable. I would recommend Penrose to anyone in need of physical therapy.'),(2318,213,'_testimonial_content','field_testimonial_content'),(2319,213,'testimonial_logo','200'),(2320,213,'_testimonial_logo','field_testimonial_logo'),(2321,213,'_yoast_wpseo_content_score','60'),(2322,214,'_edit_lock','1487891737:4'),(2323,214,'_edit_last','2'),(2324,214,'content_builder_0_content','<h1>Challenge</h1>\r\nKathleen came understanding she had this silent disease of the bones weakening but not knowing what to do safely for exercises.  She knew she needed to exercise to increase bone density but she also has arthritis making it even more challenging.  She was told by her doctor to avoid bending and limit reaching.  However, she still needed to do daily life activities.   She wanted to learn how to move her spine safely while cleaning, grocery shopping, and lifting.'),(2325,214,'_content_builder_0_content','field_left_content'),(2326,214,'content_builder_0_image','372'),(2327,214,'_content_builder_0_image','field_right_image'),(2328,214,'content_builder_1_content','<h1>Solution</h1>\r\nWe instructed her how to move her spine safely with lifting, squatting, reaching, and rolling over in bed.  She learned how to hip hinge and bend in the hips while keeping the spine straight.  She learned what motions would increase stress to the spine and place her at greater risk for a vertebral compression fracture.  She learned how to strengthen the muscles of her spine and hips to help support those areas that were showing weakened bone.  She also learned what motions to modify at her local gym classes.'),(2329,214,'_content_builder_1_content','field_center_content'),(2330,214,'content_builder_2_image','373'),(2331,214,'_content_builder_2_image','field_left_image'),(2336,214,'content_builder','a:4:{i:0;s:12:\"left_content\";i:1;s:14:\"center_content\";i:2;s:13:\"right_content\";i:3;s:14:\"center_content\";}'),(2337,214,'_content_builder','field_builder'),(2338,214,'header_heading',''),(2339,214,'_header_heading','field_heading'),(2340,214,'header_background','270'),(2341,214,'_header_background','field_background'),(2342,214,'testimonial_author','Kathleen Cannon'),(2343,214,'_testimonial_author','field_testimonial_author'),(2344,214,'testimonial_content','My expectations have been exceeded...Jennifer listens carefully...she excels in patient teaching...it has been a joy to work with all the team members of Penrose PT and I highly recommend them.'),(2345,214,'_testimonial_content','field_testimonial_content'),(2346,214,'testimonial_logo','114'),(2347,214,'_testimonial_logo','field_testimonial_logo'),(2348,214,'_yoast_wpseo_content_score','30'),(2349,215,'_edit_lock','1491242316:2'),(2350,215,'_edit_last','4'),(2351,215,'content_builder_0_content','<h1></h1>\r\n<h1>Challenge</h1>\r\nJohn Paul III, at age 11, was having constant foot pain with sports and walking.  He had a foot type that was biomechanically challenged.  He had very flat feet that were unable to handle running, jumping, and walking without pain.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>Solution</h1>\r\nAfter a thorough examination and measuring his feet we casted his feet for custom orthotics.  He neededthem for everyday use and sports.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>Result</h1>\r\nHis custom orthotics allowed him to play sports and walk/run without pain!  They also kept his legs and knees in better alignment.  This decreases his chance for additional injuries.  His family elected to enroll in the pediatric plan so they could keep getting new orthotics as he grew with less expense.  A savings of $475.  As he grows he comes in for new casting/measuring and only pays for that portion since he already purchased the next 4 pairs.'),(2352,215,'_content_builder_0_content','field_left_content'),(2353,215,'content_builder_0_image','296'),(2354,215,'_content_builder_0_image','field_right_image'),(2355,215,'content_builder_1_content','<h1>From His Parents</h1>\r\n<span class=\"\">\"Our son suffered from sore feet and legs from a young age.  He could often barely walk after baseball or basketball practice. With Jen’s expert care he was able to get the physical therapy and custom orthotics he needed to enjoy sports without pain.</span>\" -Kris Tefft\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),(2356,215,'_content_builder_1_content','field_center_content'),(2357,215,'content_builder_2_image',''),(2358,215,'_content_builder_2_image','field_left_image'),(2363,215,'content_builder','a:1:{i:0;s:12:\"left_content\";}'),(2364,215,'_content_builder','field_builder'),(2365,215,'header_heading',''),(2366,215,'_header_heading','field_heading'),(2367,215,'header_background','174'),(2368,215,'_header_background','field_background'),(2369,215,'testimonial_author','Kris Teft'),(2370,215,'_testimonial_author','field_testimonial_author'),(2371,215,'testimonial_content','Our son suffered from sore feet and legs from a young age.  He could often barely walk after baseball or basketball practice. With Jen’s expert care he was able to get the physical therapy and custom orthotics he needed to enjoy sports without pain.'),(2372,215,'_testimonial_content','field_testimonial_content'),(2373,215,'testimonial_logo','108'),(2374,215,'_testimonial_logo','field_testimonial_logo'),(2375,215,'_yoast_wpseo_content_score','90'),(2376,216,'_edit_lock','1487891896:4'),(2377,216,'_edit_last','2'),(2378,216,'content_builder_0_content','<h1>Challenge</h1>\r\nYvonne is a female in her 50s who has been trying to increase her running mileage. Unfortunately shin splints and overuse of her calf muscles kept her from success.  She knew she needed to increase her core and overall strength.  Cross Fit was helping with that but she was still unable to run farther or faster without shin or calf pain.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-403 size-medium\" src=\"https://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/core-training-1730330-e1485040092690-300x193.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"193\" />'),(2379,216,'_content_builder_0_content','field_left_content'),(2380,216,'content_builder_0_image','402'),(2381,216,'_content_builder_0_image','field_right_image'),(2382,216,'content_builder_1_content','<h1>Solution</h1>\r\nYvonne came to Penrose Physical Therapy for a gait/runner’s/movement analysis to figure out why she was overusing her calf muscles.  This movement analysis involved video with slow motion play back.  It showed her that she was over-striding, her cadence needed to increase, and she needed to have a slight lean to have her foot fall underneath her in order to decrease the shin and calf pain.  It also showed her that her hip flexors were too tight and her hip rotators were weak.  It also showed her that tight hip flexors placed her in a disadvantageous posture while running.  This posture did not allow her to use her hamstrings or gluteus maximus effectively.   All of this was explained in terms she understood and exercises and running drills were given to help her address all of these issues.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-405\" src=\"https://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/lower-extremity-angle-definitions-300x223.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"223\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),(2383,216,'_content_builder_1_content','field_center_content'),(2384,216,'content_builder_2_image','404'),(2385,216,'_content_builder_2_image','field_left_image'),(2386,216,'content_builder_2_content','<h1>Result</h1>\r\nAfter this one time movement consultation she followed the instructions including new shoes for her particular foot type.  She is now able to run with better form for longer periods of time and no shin or calf pain.'),(2387,216,'_content_builder_2_content','field_right_content'),(2388,216,'content_builder_3_content','<h1>In Her Own Words</h1>\r\n“I’m so grateful for the insight that the movement analysis provided.  I can finally run without chronic pain and I am actually enjoying it for the first time in many years!”'),(2389,216,'_content_builder_3_content','field_center_content'),(2390,216,'content_builder','a:3:{i:0;s:12:\"left_content\";i:1;s:14:\"center_content\";i:2;s:13:\"right_content\";}'),(2391,216,'_content_builder','field_builder'),(2392,216,'header_heading',''),(2393,216,'_header_heading','field_heading'),(2394,216,'header_background','312'),(2395,216,'_header_background','field_background'),(2396,216,'testimonial_author','Yvonne Fish '),(2397,216,'_testimonial_author','field_testimonial_author'),(2398,216,'testimonial_content','I’m so grateful for the insight that the movement analysis provided.  I can finally run without chronic pain and I am actually enjoying it for the first time in many years!'),(2399,216,'_testimonial_content','field_testimonial_content'),(2400,216,'testimonial_logo','108'),(2401,216,'_testimonial_logo','field_testimonial_logo'),(2402,216,'_yoast_wpseo_content_score','60'),(2403,217,'_edit_lock','1487891938:4'),(2404,217,'_edit_last','4'),(2405,217,'content_builder_0_content','<h1>Challenge</h1>\r\nSusan in her early 70s developed vestibular neuritis caused by a virus that attacked an inner ear nerve creating vertigo and hearing loss.  She came to Penrose Physical Therapy having a very difficult time even walking a straight line without stumbling all over.  She was unable to drive or go to the grocery store.  Her body would start shaking and she started to feel anxious and feel like she was having a panic attack.  She started to withdraw from public functions and crowds due to her appearance of stumbling and wobbling while walking.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-376 size-medium\" src=\"https://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Photo-Jan-20-4-28-27-PM-e1484975295263-225x300.jpg\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" />'),(2406,217,'_content_builder_0_content','field_left_content'),(2407,217,'content_builder_0_image','370'),(2408,217,'_content_builder_0_image','field_right_image'),(2409,217,'content_builder_1_content','<h1>Solution</h1>\r\nWe had to be very gradual in retraining her brain and vestibular and visual system.  She was given exercises that required her to track objects with her eyes without moving her head and then eventually with moving her head.  She started in sitting and gradually standing and eventually walking.  We then introduced walking on uneven surfaces and obstacle courses.  She learned how to slowly increase the difficulty of the vestibular home program and how to make it easier if she got too dizzy.'),(2410,217,'_content_builder_1_content','field_center_content'),(2411,217,'content_builder_2_image','320'),(2412,217,'_content_builder_2_image','field_left_image'),(2413,217,'content_builder_2_content','<h1>Result</h1>\r\nAfter a couple months she was able to drive again and return to grocery shopping without stumbling or feeling dizzy.  She returned to the gym and is able to perform her work out routines now. The nerve damage did result in some permanent hearing loss and vestibular impairment.  However, she understands how the balance work continues to retrain her brain and system to compensate and allow her to function again.'),(2414,217,'_content_builder_2_content','field_right_content'),(2415,217,'content_builder_3_content','<h1>In Her Own Words</h1>\r\n“I’m so grateful for the vestibular re -raining I received at Penrose Physical Therapy.  They were always so patient and took the time to explain why I was doing what I was doing.  They taught me how to slow down and take some control over my vertigo.”'),(2416,217,'_content_builder_3_content','field_center_content'),(2417,217,'content_builder','a:3:{i:0;s:12:\"left_content\";i:1;s:14:\"center_content\";i:2;s:13:\"right_content\";}'),(2418,217,'_content_builder','field_builder'),(2419,217,'header_heading',''),(2420,217,'_header_heading','field_heading'),(2421,217,'header_background','184'),(2422,217,'_header_background','field_background'),(2423,217,'testimonial_author','Susan Frank'),(2424,217,'_testimonial_author','field_testimonial_author'),(2425,217,'testimonial_content','“I’m so grateful for the vestibular re-training I received at Penrose Physical Therapy.  They were always so patient and took the time to explain why I was doing what I was doing.  They taught me how to slow down and take some control over my vertigo.'),(2426,217,'_testimonial_content','field_testimonial_content'),(2427,217,'testimonial_logo','108'),(2428,217,'_testimonial_logo','field_testimonial_logo'),(2429,217,'_yoast_wpseo_content_score','90'),(2430,218,'_edit_lock','1487887092:4'),(2431,218,'_edit_last','4'),(2432,218,'content_builder_0_content','<h1>Challenge</h1>\r\nTammy, age early 50s, had TMJ dysfunction of clicking, popping, and her jaw getting stuck for about 20 years.  She also suffered from migraine headaches for years managed by prescription medication.  She was told nothing could be done for her TMJ other than surgery.  Tammy read the outcomes on TMJ surgery were not very promising and elected not to do surgery.  Her condition was worsening where her jaw would get stuck several times a day and she was starting to avoid eating chewy foods.'),(2433,218,'_content_builder_0_content','field_left_content'),(2434,218,'content_builder_0_image','369'),(2435,218,'_content_builder_0_image','field_right_image'),(2436,218,'content_builder_1_content','<h1>Solution</h1>\r\nTammy worked at a computer and we needed to address how she was sitting at the computer/desk.  We taught her how to hold her mouth/tongue/neck while in sitting.  This causes relaxation of the clenching muscles of her jaw and decreases the tension in her neck muscles.  We performed manual therapy to release the tight muscles in her jaw/face and we released the tight muscles in her neck.  Joint mobilizations also helped increase her joint mobility and range of motion.  Tammy learned exercises to strengthen the weak opening muscles of her jaw which allowed her to eat more foods without pain.  Her migraines also improved with posture muscle strengthening of her neck and upper back.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-409\" src=\"https://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Photo-Oct-03-12-23-36-PM-e1485048121725-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),(2437,218,'_content_builder_1_content','field_center_content'),(2438,218,'content_builder_2_image','368'),(2439,218,'_content_builder_2_image','field_left_image'),(2440,218,'content_builder_2_content','<h1>Result</h1>\r\nIn 15 visits she reported 80% improvement and migraines were no longer daily.  She can now eat most foods without having to stop and help her jaw get back in place.  Tammy is very grateful for the posture correction that she now maintains at work as well as the daily exercises that keep her TMJ and migraines in check.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-410\" src=\"https://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Photo-Jan-20-1-01-31-PM-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />'),(2441,218,'_content_builder_2_content','field_right_content'),(2442,218,'content_builder_3_content','<h1>In Her Own Words</h1>\r\n“I’m grateful for Penrose Physical Therapy as I didn’t think anything could help my TMJ or make a significant impact on my migraines.  The daily exercises and posture have made a significant improvement in my life.  I wish more people knew that physical therapy can help with TMJ and migraines.\"'),(2443,218,'_content_builder_3_content','field_center_content'),(2444,218,'content_builder','a:3:{i:0;s:12:\"left_content\";i:1;s:14:\"center_content\";i:2;s:13:\"right_content\";}'),(2445,218,'_content_builde