veral great massage therapists in the community that we can refer you to.'),(2682,77,'_content_builder_2_content','field_right_content'),(2683,77,'content_builder_3_heading','Why choose us?'),(2684,77,'_content_builder_3_heading','field_comparison_heading'),(2685,77,'content_builder_3_content','Jennifer Penrose, DPT, OCS, MTC and Kristen Weaver, MSPT, Cert MDT, CMPT are both certified manual therapists.  Manual therapy is specialized techniques where the therapist uses their hands to manipulate joints and soft tissue structures in order to increase mobility and decrease pain.  Manual therapy can also help decrease swelling with a special massage technique.  Chris Edwards, PTA our assistant also has training in manual techniques to assist in your recovery.\r\n\r\nDr. Penrose and her assistant Chris Edwards are <strong>Graston Trained</strong> and will use both metal and plastic instruments for soft tissue mobilization in addition to their hands.  We can even teach you how to use the plastic instruments should you want to purchase your own for home use.\r\n\r\n<strong>Graston technique</strong> uses specially-designed stainless steel instruments, along with appropriate therapeutic exercise, to specifically detect and effectively treat areas exhibiting soft tissue fibrosis or chronic inflammation. The instruments also are used diagnostically to follow the kinetic chain, to locate and treat the cause of the symptom as well as the specific area of pain.\r\n\r\n<strong>IASTM</strong> is Instrumented Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization with use of ceramic, plastic, or metal instruments.  Graston Technique® is a unique, evidence-based form of instrument-assisted soft tissue mobilization that enables clinicians to effectively address scar tissue and fascial restrictions through comprehensive training, resulting in improved patient outcomes.\r\n\r\nThe Penrose Physical Therapy team believes manual therapy is vital in restoring mobility and decreasing your pain.  We may also determine that in addition to physical therapy you may benefit from massage therapy.  Ryan Critser, LMP is our massage therapist on Tuesdays at Penrose Physical Therapy. You can read more about Ryan on our Team page. We also know several great massage therapists in the community that we can refer you to.'),(2686,77,'_content_builder_3_content','field_service_content'),(2687,77,'content_builder_3_video_heading','Injury Rehabilitation Success Story'),(2688,77,'_content_builder_3_video_heading','field_service_video_heading'),(2689,77,'content_builder_3_video','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ppm5_AGtbTo'),(2690,77,'_content_builder_3_video','field_service_video'),(2691,77,'content_builder_3_video_image','19'),(2692,77,'_content_builder_3_video_image','field_service_video_image'),(2693,77,'content_builder_4_heading','Why choose us?'),(2694,77,'_content_builder_4_heading','field_comparison_heading'),(2695,77,'content_builder_4_comparison_table_0_comparison_text','Treatment'),(2696,77,'_content_builder_4_comparison_table_0_comparison_text','field_comparison_text'),(2697,77,'content_builder_4_comparison_table_0_typical_text','Many therapists have not spent years in additional training learning how to best use their  hands manually to alleviate your pain and increase your range of motion.'),(2698,77,'_content_builder_4_comparison_table_0_typical_text','field_comparison_typical'),(2699,77,'content_builder_4_comparison_table_1_comparison_text','Resources & Support'),(2700,77,'_content_builder_4_comparison_table_1_comparison_text','field_comparison_text'),(2701,77,'content_builder_4_comparison_table_1_typical_text','Many therapists do not spend the hands on time your diagnosis needs to  increase range of motion and promote healing.'),(2702,77,'_content_builder_4_comparison_table_1_typical_text','field_comparison_typical'),(2703,77,'content_builder_4_comparison_table_2_comparison_text','Cost'),(2704,77,'_content_builder_4_comparison_table_2_comparison_text','field_comparison_text'