ent_builder_3_cases_1_case','field_case'),(3259,82,'content_builder_3_cases','2'),(3260,82,'_content_builder_3_cases','field_cases'),(3261,333,'content_builder_0_content','<h1>Skilled Treatment.  Supportive Atmosphere. Invaluable Advice.</h1>\r\n<strong>Vertigo</strong> is caused by issues with the inner ear—such as Benign Paroxysmal Positional Vertigo (BPPV), which develops as tiny calcium particles build up in the ear canals; Meniere’s disease, which is caused by fluid pressure in the ear; and Vestibular neuritis, a viral infection of the inner ear nerves.\r\n\r\nThe primary symptom of vertigo (permanent dizziness) is a feeling of spinning, you may feel tilted yourself or you may feel that the world is swaying, which causes an unbalanced sensation that you are being pulled in one direction.  This makes it very difficult to walk, drive, or go places.\r\n\r\nVertigo is very debilitating and leaves you feeling out of control.  Penrose Physical Therapy will help you with treatments that work quickly and also give you information as to what is happening and why.  Information helps to relieve the anxiety and panic attacks.'),(3262,333,'_content_builder_0_content','field_left_content'),(3263,333,'content_builder_0_image','321'),(3264,333,'_content_builder_0_image','field_right_image'),(3265,333,'content_builder_1_content','<h5 style=\"text-align: left;\">Possible symptoms of vertigo</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">headaches, fatigue, nausea, sweating</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">dizziness, hearing loss</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">twitch eyes, ear pressure, ringing in the ears</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">panic attacks</li>\r\n</ul>'),(3266,333,'_content_builder_1_content','field_center_content'),(3267,333,'content_builder_2_content','<strong>Impaired balance</strong> is not only caused by vertigo.  We treat balance with many other conditions as well.  Decreased balance leads to increased risk of falling.  Can you 