'Listening to Patients. Achieving Lifelong Results.\r\n\r\nWe are orthopedic physical therapy specialists.  We achieve results quickly.  We teach you how to maintain muscle and joint health for a lifetime.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-111 size-large\" src=\"https://penrosept.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Homepageheroimage-1-1024x594.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"594\" />'),(4653,563,'_content_builder_0_content','field_accordion_left_content'),(4654,563,'content_builder_0_right_heading','Our Values'),(4655,563,'_content_builder_0_right_heading','field_accordion_right_heading'),(4656,563,'content_builder_0_accordion_0_accordion_heading','We listen to you'),(4657,563,'_content_builder_0_accordion_0_accordion_heading','field_accordion_heading'),(4658,563,'content_builder_0_accordion_0_accordion_content','<p class=\"p1\">We want to establish trust and rapport by listening to you first.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Your concerns will be heard and addressed.</p>'),(4659,563,'_content_builder_0_accordion_0_accordion_content','field_accordion_content'),(4660,563,'content_builder_0_accordion_1_accordion_heading','We utilize the latest evidence'),(4661,563,'_content_builder_0_accordion_1_accordion_heading','field_accordion_heading'),(4662,563,'content_builder_0_accordion_1_accordion_content','<p class=\"p1\">It is the ethical way to treat patients.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>You are paying for results.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We use evidenced based treatment and provide standardized outcome measures for you and the payors.</p>'),(4663,563,'_content_builder_0_accordion_1_accordion_content','field_accordion_content'),(4664,563,'content_builder_0_accordion_2_accordion_heading','We believe in a hands on approach'),(4665,563,'_content_builder_0_accordion_2_accordion_heading','field_accordion_heading'),(4666,563,'content_builder_0_accordion_2_accordion_content','<p class=\"p1\">We use our hands to increase your mobility and decrease pain.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We use our hands to provide guidance during exercise and movements to help you feel which muscle you should use in which sequence.</p>'),(4667,563,'_content_builder_0_accordion_2_accordion_content','field_accordion_content'),(4668,563,'content_builder_0_accordion_3_accordion_heading','We teach patients an active program'),(4669,563,'_content_builder_0_accordion_3_accordion_heading','field_accordion_heading'),(4670,563,'content_builder_0_accordion_3_accordion_content','<p class=\"p1\">Motion is lotion.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The musculoskeletal system needs range of motion to provide nutrients to the joints and tissues in order to heal.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We will teach a home exercise program that restores mobility in a gradual process that will encourage tissue healing.</p>'),(4671,563,'_content_builder_0_accordion_3_accordion_content','field_accordion_content'),(4672,563,'content_builder_0_accordion_4_accordion_heading','We educate patients'),(4673,563,'_content_builder_0_accordion_4_accordion_heading','field_accordion_heading'),(4674,563,'content_builder_0_accordion_4_accordion_content','<p class=\"p1\">We want to answer your 5 basic questions.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>What is creating the pain?<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Why did it develop?<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>How can physical therapy help?<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>How long will this take?<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>How do I prevent further injury? We welcome your questions.</p>'),(4675,563,'_content_builder_0_accordion_4_accordion_content','field_accordion_content'),(4676,563,'content_builder_0_accordion','5'),(4677,563,'_content_builder_0_accordion','field_accordion'),(4678,563,'content_builder_1_heading','Our Team'),(4679,563,'_content_builder_1_heading','field_team_heading'),(4680,563,'content_builder_1_members_0_image','22'),(4681,563,'_content_builder_1_members_0_image','field_team_image'),(4682,563,'content_builder_1_members_0_image_hover','49'),(4683,563,'_content_builder_1_members_0_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(4684,563,'content_builder_1_members_0_first_name','Jennifer'),(4685,563,'_content_builder_1_members_0_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(4686,563,'content_builder_1_members_0_last_name','Penrose'),(4687,563,'_content_builder_1_members_0_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(4688,563,'content_builder_1_members_0_position','DPT, OCS, MTC, Owner'),(4689,563,'_content_builder_1_members_0_position','field_team_position'),(4690,563,'content_builder_1_members_0_email','jennifer@penrosept.com'),(4691,563,'_content_builder_1_members_0_email','field_team_email'),(4692,563,'content_builder_1_members_0_professional_bio','Dr.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Jennifer Penrose has been a physical therapist since 2001 with a Doctorate in Physical Therapy, board certified in orthopedics (OCS), and manual certified (MTC).   She enjoys working with a variety of sports and orthopedic injuries.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Her manual therapy certification (MTC) provides her with the hands on skills needed to mobilize joints and soft tissues.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“I love working with my hands to increase patient’s mobility and decrease their pain.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>\r\n\r\nShe also enjoys looking at how patients move in order to determine what dysfunctional movement pattern may be causing their pain.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“We are movement analysts or mechanics with the human body.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>\r\n\r\nShe also enjoys teaching patients.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“Patients have less fear and anxiety and less pain about their injury when we explain the normal process of healing and pain and what to expect along this rehabilitation journey.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We want to make this a comfortable, learning, and successful process.”\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Dr. Penrose’s reputation and expertise has gained her a broad base of referral relationships with various health providers, specifically in orthopedics, internal medicine, family practice, and podiatry.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">She also enjoys working with the running population evaluating running mechanics and continues to run half marathons herself and give running workshops to the public.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">------</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Board Certification in Orthopedics:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>March 2005.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Only 6% of all licensed physical therapists are board certified in orthopedics.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Undergraduate Education:</strong>\r\nNorthwestern College, Orange City, IA\r\nBachelor of Arts, Magna Cum Laude, May 1998\r\nHonors and tennis scholarships</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Physical Therapy School:</strong>\r\nEastern Washington University, Spokane, WA\r\nMaster’s in Physical Therapy, Summa Cum Laude, Dec. 2000\r\nCASE scholarship, AMBUCS scholarship, &amp; John Joy scholarship</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Post-graduate Doctorate:</strong>\r\nTransitional Doctorate of Physical Therapy\r\nUniversity of St. Augustine, FL April 2006</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Publication:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Hennington G, Johnson J, Penrose J, Barr K, McMulkin ML, Vander Linden DW.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Effect of bench height on sit to stand in children with disabilities and children with cerebral palsy.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Arch Phys Med Rehabil.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>2004: Jan;85(1):70-6.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Click here for <a href=\"http://penrose1.wpengine.com/speaking-engagements/\">Speaking Engagements</a>\r\n</strong></p>'),(4693,563,'_content_builder_1_members_0_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(4694,563,'content_builder_1_members_0_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Power of One</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Choosing to See</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why I live in the South Sound:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Mountains, ocean, close to Seattle and Portland.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite sports moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>When my 8 year old son qualified &amp; participated in the USATF Junior Olympic Cross Country National Championships.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst injury ever suffered:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>13mm disc herniation at L5-S1 that could not be rehabilitated resulting in a micro-discectomy surgery.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When I am not at work, I am:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>With my 3 boys and spouse, running, traveling, on the beach in the sun, eating great food, or shopping.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best advice I\'ve ever received:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>You can only control 2 things in life:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Attitude and Effort.</p>'),(4695,563,'_content_builder_1_members_0_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(4696,563,'content_builder_1_members_1_image','23'),(4697,563,'_content_builder_1_members_1_image','field_team_image'),(4698,563,'content_builder_1_members_1_image_hover','48'),(4699,563,'_content_builder_1_members_1_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(4700,563,'content_builder_1_members_1_first_name','Chris'),(4701,563,'_content_builder_1_members_1_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(4702,563,'content_builder_1_members_1_last_name','Edwards'),(4703,563,'_content_builder_1_members_1_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(4704,563,'content_builder_1_members_1_position','PTA'),(4705,563,'_content_builder_1_members_1_position','field_team_position'),(4706,563,'content_builder_1_members_1_email','chris@penrosept.com'),(4707,563,'_content_builder_1_members_1_email','field_team_email'),(4708,563,'content_builder_1_members_1_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\">Chris Edwards is a Licensed Physical Therapist Assistant.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He assists the physical therapists in treating their patients.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  We</span> are a team that communicates regularly regarding each patient’s status and progress.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Chris is an expert at challenging patients with progressive exercises without increasing pain.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“I enjoy finding new ways to work muscles that patients find challenging and at the same time applicable to their goals.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He has training in Graston technique and kinesiotaping.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He is also certified in functional range conditioning.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He has been a vital piece to the success and team at Penrose Physical Therapy.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He truly loves to learn the latest evidence and techniques in physical therapy which benefits the patients and our practice.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">As a child Chris grew up north of Seattle but moved to Kansas with his family when he was 12, where he would later meet his beautiful wife and they would begin raising their five children.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>He became a PTA in Kansas where he graduated with Honors as member of the Phi Theta Kappa with multiple Academic awards including top two in his class to pass state boards.</p>'),(4709,563,'_content_builder_1_members_1_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(4710,563,'content_builder_1_members_1_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>The Family Man</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>I confess I read mostly physical therapy articles and research latest treatment techniques.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I also love to read about new recipes.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I love great food!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why you I live in the South Sound:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>I grew up here and knew at some point I would return with my family.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite sports moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>The Seahawks first Superbowl win in 2014 of course!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst injury I have suffered:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>A broken wrist playing basket-ball when I was 16 with my arm casted all the way to my shoulder.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When I am not at work, I am:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Enjoying time with my 5 kids and amazing spouse!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Watching the Seahawks!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Cooking.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best advice I\'ve ever received:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>The kind of person you are is not defined by the choices you’ve made and your future is not determined by your past.</p>'),(4711,563,'_content_builder_1_members_1_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(4712,563,'content_builder_1_members_2_image','50'),(4713,563,'_content_builder_1_members_2_image','field_team_image'),(4714,563,'content_builder_1_members_2_image_hover','51'),(4715,563,'_content_builder_1_members_2_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(4716,563,'content_builder_1_members_2_first_name','Kristen'),(4717,563,'_content_builder_1_members_2_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(4718,563,'content_builder_1_members_2_last_name','Weaver'),(4719,563,'_content_builder_1_members_2_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(4720,563,'content_builder_1_members_2_position','MSPT, Cert MDT, CMPT, Part Time Physical Therapist'),(4721,563,'_content_builder_1_members_2_position','field_team_position'),(4722,563,'content_builder_1_members_2_email','trinitravelhc@gmail.com'),(4723,563,'_content_builder_1_members_2_email','field_team_email'),(4724,563,'content_builder_1_members_2_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><b>Grand Valley State University </b>Allendale, MI</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Master of Science in Physical Therapy Spring 2004</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Bachelor of Science in Health Sciences Spring 2002</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Special Certifications\r\n</b>Certified Manual Therapist (NAIOMT) August 2013</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">McKenzie Certified Therapist October 2006</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Kristen has been a PT since 2004 and has quite a variety of experiences including home health, skilled nursing, and primarily outpatient orthopedics.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She has found that orthopedics has great diversity in working with her hands and the neuromuscular system as a whole.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“I have an interest in manual therapy and exercise to re-train the neural connections between the brain and muscles to gain optimal function.”</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">She is committed to finding the root cause(s) to a patient’s pain or mobility problem.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“It is important to me to discover the specific impairments a patient may have and then develop an individualized treatment plan that is practical and fun!”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We are excited to have her on the team.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Kristen works part time so she can balance life with her 3 kids!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She enjoys the outdoors and time with her husband.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Zumba is also a fun activity that allows her to keep up with her active kids.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She also enjoys quiet time studying the Bible and volunteering for MOPS (Mothers of Preschoolers).</p>'),(4725,563,'_content_builder_1_members_2_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(4726,563,'content_builder_1_members_2_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Inspirational movies like “The Prayer Room”</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Inspirational books like Karen Kingsbury books and Ted Dekker books</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why I live in the South Sound:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>I love the variety of landscape/nature.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I love the mountains, the lakes, the rivers, rainforest, the ocean.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite sports moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>I loved competing in rock climbing competitions with friends in college.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst injury I have suffered:</strong> Childbirth!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>It was quite a recovery process each time.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When I\'m not at work, I am:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Enjoying time with my 3 young kids and spouse! <span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I may also be out camping, hiking, water and snow skiing, rock climbing, mountain biking, gardening, and creating adventures.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best advice I\'ve ever received:</strong> Love your husband by showing that you respect him.</p>'),(4727,563,'_content_builder_1_members_2_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(4728,563,'content_builder_1_members_3_image','36'),(4729,563,'_content_builder_1_members_3_image','field_team_image'),(4730,563,'content_builder_1_members_3_image_hover','53'),(4731,563,'_content_builder_1_members_3_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(4732,563,'content_builder_1_members_3_first_name','Lerae'),(4733,563,'_content_builder_1_members_3_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(4734,563,'content_builder_1_members_3_last_name','Ketchum'),(4735,563,'_content_builder_1_members_3_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(4736,563,'content_builder_1_members_3_position','Administrative Assistant'),(4737,563,'_content_builder_1_members_3_position','field_team_position'),(4738,563,'content_builder_1_members_3_email','lerae@penrosept.com'),(4739,563,'_content_builder_1_members_3_email','field_team_email'),(4740,563,'content_builder_1_members_3_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\">Lerae graduated from local Timberline High School &amp; will continue her education in Art Therapy.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Along with being on the Honor Roll all four years of high school, she played volleyball for multiple teams and assisted in coaching a co-ed softball team.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Lerae embodies the culture at Penrose Physical Therapy.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She loves to help others and wants to bring a smile to each person she meets.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">She has volunteered with many different groups; Rotary, assisting with care taking, and many church functions.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In working at Penrose &amp; Associates Lerae greets everyone warmly and hopes to be an encouragement to them from the moment they enter the front door.</p>'),(4741,563,'_content_builder_1_members_3_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(4742,563,'content_builder_1_members_3_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Seven Pounds</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>1984 by George Orwell</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why I live in the South Sound:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Grew up here and can’t imagine being far away from family!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite sports moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>In middle school I was finally able to get my serve over the net (7’ 12”)!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst injury I have suffered:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>At circuit city my mom told me to sit down on a shelving unit and the whole thing fell down fracturing my leg and ankle.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When I am not at work, I am:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>At the gym or enjoying time with my family and my dog.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best advice I\'ve ever received:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Don’t stress about what you cannot change, but put your energy into what you can and God will take care of the rest.</p>'),(4743,563,'_content_builder_1_members_3_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(4744,563,'content_builder_1_members_4_image','46'),(4745,563,'_content_builder_1_members_4_image','field_team_image'),(4746,563,'content_builder_1_members_4_image_hover','47'),(4747,563,'_content_builder_1_members_4_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(4748,563,'content_builder_1_members_4_first_name','Catie'),(4749,563,'_content_builder_1_members_4_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(4750,563,'content_builder_1_members_4_last_name','Lynn'),(4751,563,'_content_builder_1_members_4_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(4752,563,'content_builder_1_members_4_position','Part-Time Physical Therapy Aide and Front Office'),(4753,563,'_content_builder_1_members_4_position','field_team_position'),(4754,563,'content_builder_1_members_4_email','catie@penrosept.com'),(4755,563,'_content_builder_1_members_4_email','field_team_email'),(4756,563,'content_builder_1_members_4_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\">Catie joins our team after graduating high-school 1 year early.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She enjoys helping and serving others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She is exploring what schooling or career she will do next.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“I am honored to be part of a team that enjoys what they do and part of something where you can see people get better at each visit.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Her compassion and willingness to serve is a joy to have as we mentor her along in the journey of what life has for her next steps.</p>'),(4757,563,'_content_builder_1_members_4_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(4758,563,'content_builder_1_members_4_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Original Ben Hur</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Les Miserables</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why I live in the South Sound:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Currently living with extended family in WA.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I am grateful to live and work in healthy/supportive environments to help determine the next steps in my life for school or career.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite sports moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>When my little sister scored her first points in a basketball game.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>She was so thrilled.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The joy watching her was so fun.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst injury I have suffered:</strong> When I accidentally cut open one of the tendons in my hand.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When I am not at work, I am:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Reading, writing/journaling, or talking with family.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best advice I\'ve ever received:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>It’s impossible to please everyone, but don’t worry about it. You’re not responsible for other people’s feelings.</p>'),(4759,563,'_content_builder_1_members_4_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(4760,563,'content_builder_1_members_5_image','358'),(4761,563,'_content_builder_1_members_5_image','field_team_image'),(4762,563,'content_builder_1_members_5_image_hover','355'),(4763,563,'_content_builder_1_members_5_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(4764,563,'content_builder_1_members_5_first_name','Marissa'),(4765,563,'_content_builder_1_members_5_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(4766,563,'content_builder_1_members_5_last_name','Ang'),(4767,563,'_content_builder_1_members_5_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(4768,563,'content_builder_1_members_5_position','Athletic Trainer/Physical Therapy Aide'),(4769,563,'_content_builder_1_members_5_position','field_team_position'),(4770,563,'content_builder_1_members_5_email','marissa@penrosept.com'),(4771,563,'_content_builder_1_members_5_email','field_team_email'),(4772,563,'content_builder_1_members_5_professional_bio','Marissa Ang joined Penrose &amp; Associates in January of 2017.  She grew up In Olympia, Washington and graduated from Olympia High School in 2009. Marissa graduated from the University of North Dakota in May of 2016 with a Bachelors in Athletic Training.  After graduation she made the move to Chicago to begin her career in Athletic Training.  She found herself missing her family and recently moved back to the Pacific Northwest.\r\n\r\nMarissa has 3 years experience working with Division 1 athletes and has enjoyed watching people get better and continue to participate in the activities they love. She is excited to continue helping others get back the strength they need to fulfill daily functions of life.'),(4773,563,'_content_builder_1_members_5_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(4774,563,'content_builder_1_members_5_personal_bio','<strong>Favorite movie:</strong> Step Brothers\r\n\r\n<strong>Favorite book:</strong> The Great Gatsby\r\n\r\n<strong>Why I live in the South Sound:</strong> I love the beauty of the PNW.\r\n\r\n<strong>Favorite sports moment:</strong> Being in Chicago when the Cubs won the World Series\r\n\r\n<strong>Worst injury I have suffered:</strong> Sprained ankle at the finish line of state cross country meet\r\n\r\n<strong>When I am not at work, I am:</strong> Working out and hanging out with my family and friends\r\n\r\n<strong>Best advice I have ever received:</strong> “Actions speaks louder than words”'),(4775,563,'_content_builder_1_members_5_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(4776,563,'content_builder_1_members_6_image','401'),(4777,563,'_content_builder_1_members_6_image','field_team_image'),(4778,563,'content_builder_1_members_6_image_hover','54'),(4779,563,'_content_builder_1_members_6_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(4780,563,'content_builder_1_members_6_first_name','Ryan'),(4781,563,'_content_builder_1_members_6_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(4782,563,'content_builder_1_members_6_last_name','Critser'),(4783,563,'_content_builder_1_members_6_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(4784,563,'content_builder_1_members_6_position','LMP - Licensed Massage Practitioner'),(4785,563,'_content_builder_1_members_6_position','field_team_position'),(4786,563,'content_builder_1_members_6_email','dreaandryanc@gmail.com'),(4787,563,'_content_builder_1_members_6_email','field_team_email'),(4788,563,'content_builder_1_members_6_professional_bio','<p class=\"p1\">Ryan graduated from Brenneke School of Massage in 2002. He has considerable experience working with injured clients in clinical settings such as chiropractic and at Penrose PT.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">He provides a safe environment where he listens to his client\'s goals and concerns. Comfort levels are taken into consideration for all ranges, from first time clients to long time veterans. “Each client is different in their expectation and tolerance for massage therapy; I listen to them and adjust the massage according to what they need and tolerate.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Ryan is trained in a variety of techniques including: treatment of various orthopedic injuries, sport related injuries, nationally certified in pregnancy massage, myofascial deep tissue, trigger point, and relaxing Swedish massage. Ryan also uses moist hot packs to ensure client\'s maximum comfort during the massage process.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Ryan is a big family man! He has been married to his wife for eight amazing years and is a father to a fantastic seven year old daughter.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">**Ryan accepts a majority of all insurance plans including Regence. He is available at Penrose Physical Therapy on Tuesdays. Cash Clients: 1 hour massage - $60.00; 30 minute massage - $35.00</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Please contact Ryan directly, as he manages his own patient schedule: 360-584-6086</p>'),(4789,563,'_content_builder_1_members_6_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(4790,563,'content_builder_1_members_6_personal_bio','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Movie:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Goonies</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite Book:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Where the wild things are (yes it is a children’s book but it’s an escape for me!)</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why you live in the South Sound:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>Born in WA and raised by a single mom!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We made it work as a team!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Favorite sports moment:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>When Richard Sherman blocked Crabtree’s pass in the end zone during a playoff game.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Worst injury I have suffered:</strong> Broken left collar bone in 5<sup>th</sup> grade.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>When I am not at work, I am:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Working or studying.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I prefer to be with my amazing wife and daughter!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>“I’m a family man and a workaholic!”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">   </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Best advice I\'ve ever received:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></strong>Be bold and mighty forces will come to your aid.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>May the force be with you.</p>'),(4791,563,'_content_builder_1_members_6_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(4792,563,'content_builder_1_members_7_image','44'),(4793,563,'_content_builder_1_members_7_image','field_team_image'),(4794,563,'content_builder_1_members_7_image_hover','45'),(4795,563,'_content_builder_1_members_7_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(4796,563,'content_builder_1_members_7_first_name','Andrew'),(4797,563,'_content_builder_1_members_7_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(4798,563,'content_builder_1_members_7_last_name','Blagg'),(4799,563,'_content_builder_1_members_7_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(4800,563,'content_builder_1_members_7_position','Clinical Exercise Physiologist'),(4801,563,'_content_builder_1_members_7_position','field_team_position'),(4802,563,'content_builder_1_members_7_email','andyblagg@yahoo.com'),(4803,563,'_content_builder_1_members_7_email','field_team_email'),(4804,563,'content_builder_1_members_7_professional_bio','Based on my research and experience, I am convinced that exercise is an extremely powerful measure for preventing the development of health conditions such as musculoskeletal dysfunction (e.g. low-back pain, arthritis), obesity, diabetes, heart disease and osteoporosis. Exercise is also a very effective post-rehabilitative therapy.\r\n\r\nIt would be my pleasure to help you with a safe and effective exercise program. If you are interested, please call (206) 476-2698 or email andyblagg@yahoo.com for a free consultation.\r\n<table border=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Training Hours</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Monday</td>\r\n<td>5:30pm - 7:00pm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tuesday</td>\r\n<td>4:00pm - 7:00pm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Thursday</td>\r\n<td>4:00pm - 7:00pm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Friday</td>\r\n<td>5:30pm - 7:00pm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Saturday</td>\r\n<td>8:00am - 12:00pm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>'),(4805,563,'_content_builder_1_members_7_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(4806,563,'content_builder_1_members_7_personal_bio','<strong>Favorite Movie: </strong>The Deer Hunter\r\n\r\n<strong>Favorite Book: </strong>The Systems View of Life.\r\n\r\n<strong>Why I live in the South Sound: </strong>I grew up in TX but dreamed of moving to the Pacific Northwest for as long as I can remember. The opportunity arose a little over a year ago. I took advantage of that opportunity.\r\n\r\n<strong>Favorite sports moment: </strong>In Little League, I was running full speed from first to second after the batter hit the ball. The ball was hit to second, so it was clear that I would be out. However, instead of accepting the inevitability of the out, I slowed down as if I was going to just let the second baseman tag me. I jumped over the second baseman’s glove and onto the base at the last moment. I was safe!\r\n\r\n<strong>Worst injury I have suffered: </strong>I injured my shoulder due to an accident on my road bike.\r\n\r\n<strong>When I am not at work, I am: </strong>I enjoy broadening my knowledge base through interdisciplinary studies. I enjoy meditation and outdoor activities such as hiking, biking and kayaking.\r\n\r\n<strong>Best advice I’ve ever received: </strong>Life is about experiences.  From my grandfather; it reminds me to retain a sense of adventure throughout life.'),(4807,563,'_content_builder_1_members_7_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(4808,563,'content_builder_1_members_8_image','359'),(4809,563,'_content_builder_1_members_8_image','field_team_image'),(4810,563,'content_builder_1_members_8_image_hover','360'),(4811,563,'_content_builder_1_members_8_image_hover','field_team_image_hover'),(4812,563,'content_builder_1_members_8_first_name','Trina'),(4813,563,'_content_builder_1_members_8_first_name','field_team_first_name'),(4814,563,'content_builder_1_members_8_last_name','Fykerud'),(4815,563,'_content_builder_1_members_8_last_name','field_team_last_name'),(4816,563,'content_builder_1_members_8_position','Billing Specialist'),(4817,563,'_content_builder_1_members_8_position','field_team_position'),(4818,563,'content_builder_1_members_8_email','trina@progressivebillingspecialists.com'),(4819,563,'_content_builder_1_members_8_email','field_team_email'),(4820,563,'content_builder_1_members_8_professional_bio','Progressive Billing Specialists has been doing Physical Therapy billing for 16 years. Trina Fykerud, owner of Progressive Billing Specialists, received her BS degree in Business Administration from WWU in 1991, with a concentration in Human Resource Management and Entrepreneurial Business.\r\n\r\nPrior to starting her business, Trina worked for St. Joseph Home Health Care as a Reimbursement Specialist. She worked directly with case managers to get approval for home care and met with patients at the UW Hospital to help them understand their insurance benefits prior to being discharged.\r\n\r\nTrina also spent a few years as a certified personal trainer and nutrition consultant. She can be reached by phone at <strong>360-863-6923</strong> or by email at <strong>trina@progressivebillingspecialists.com</strong>'),(4821,563,'_content_builder_1_members_8_professional_bio','field_team_professional'),(4822,563,'content_builder_1_members_8_personal_bio','<p class=\"\"><span class=\"\"><strong>Favorite movie:</strong>  Home for the Holidays</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\"><span class=\"\"><strong>Favorite book:</strong>  In the Garden of Beasts</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\"><span class=\"\"><strong>Why I live in the PNW:</strong>  I grew up in WA and met my husband, who also grew up in WA, at WWU.  My mother-in-law and 101 year old grandmother-in-law are here as well, so we enjoy having as much time with them as possible.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\"><span class=\"\"><strong>Favorite sports moment: </strong> At 30 years old I decided to take up rowing, and I fell in love with it.  My first time racing through the Montlake Cut in Seattle was unforgettable.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\"><span class=\"\"><strong>Worst injury ever suffered: </strong> Getting kicked in the mouth when I was 3 years old.  To this day I still have ongoing issues from it.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\"><span class=\"\"><strong>When I am not at work I am: </strong> Spending time with my 2 kids, hiking, reading, baking, gardening, and enjoying my menagerie of animals (a bunny, a cat, and a French bulldog).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\"><span class=\"\"><strong>Best advice I’ve ever received: </strong> It’s good to have a plan, but always be ready to punt.</span></p>'),(4823,563,'_content_builder_1_members_8_personal_bio','field_team_personal'),(4824,563,'content_builder_1_members','9'),(4825,563,'_content_builder_1_members','field_members'),(4826,563,'content_builder_2_content','<h3>Tour Our Office</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[ipanorama id=\"161\" width=\"100%\" height=\"470px\"]</p>'),(4827,563,'_content_builder_2_content','field_center_content'),(4828,563,'content_builder','a:3