:23:27','',215,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/orthoticstanceFEAT.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(340,6,'2017-02-02 00:09:07','2017-02-02 00:09:07','Hamstring strains are the most common type of sports injury and most of you have experienced one at some point.  Hamstring strains are most often due to a shortened or lack of flexibility, and strength deficits and then throw in insufficient warm up, training error, fatigue and previous injury and your asking for months of agony.  Recovery and rehab after a hamstring strain is tricky and most will experience lingering effects or re injury due to scar tissue that has permanently altered the strength and flexibility of the muscle so the manner in which we rehab is important.\r\n\r\nMore than 80 % of all hamstring injuries have been linked to late swing phase of running due to lack of eccentric con-tractability of the muscle and ability to absorb force so like with any other training or rehabilitation the manner in which we load the muscles needs to be specific if we are to expect adaption and change to take place.\r\n\r\nEccentric training does just that,','Bulletproof Your Hamstrings','','draft','open','open','','bullet-proof-hamstrings','','','2017-02-10 20:39:34','2017-02-10 20:39:34','',0,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/?p=340',0,'post','',0),(342,4,'2017-01-17 02:04:59','2017-01-17 02:04:59','','lake-1741021_1280','','inherit','open','closed','','lake-1741021_1280','','','2017-01-22 04:13:29','2017-01-22 04:13:29','',79,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/lake-1741021_1280.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(343,4,'2017-01-17 02:05:00','2017-01-17 02:05:00','','mount-rainier-1740525_1280','','inherit','open','closed','','mount-rainier-1740525_1280','','','2017-01-17 02:05:00','2017-01-17 02:05:00','',79,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mount-rainier-1740525_1280.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(344,4,'2017-01-17 02:05:02','2017-01-17 02:05: