pg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(399,3,'2016-07-01 21:54:10','2016-07-01 21:54:10','<p class=\"p1\">Dr. Jennifer Penrose has presented at numerous seminars and with many local surgeons. She enjoys being involved in the community and educating community members about the benefits of physical therapy.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Osteoporosis and Osteoarthritis: </strong>Presented at Jubilee Community in Lacey, WA January 2017.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Shoulder rehabilitation:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"><strong> </strong> </span>impingement/bursitis, rotator cuff tendonitis &amp; repairs, shoulder instabilities, and shoulder osteoarthritis. In conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Trent McKay, MD March 2008.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Total knee replacement rehabilitation:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Anthony Agtarap, MD November 2007 &amp; again with Dr. Helpenstell in 2009.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Spinal Instabilities:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Non-surgical treatment.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Presented at Sports Medicine Conference to primary care providers in conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Chris Peterson, DO April 2006.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Ankle sprains and chronic ankle instability:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Presented at Sports Medicine Conference to primary care providers in conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Steve Snow, MD May 2004.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Tennis injuries:</strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>rehabilitation and prevention.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Thomas Helpenstell, MD in 2003 and then again in 2004 with orthopedic surgeon Steve Snow, MD.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Osteoporosis and falling:</strong> Get informed about osteoporosis, risk of falls, and osteoarthritis.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Presented at the YMCA 2004.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Traumatic Shoulder Dislocations:</strong> non-operative management, rotator cuff rehabilitation.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Presented at Sports Medicine conference to primary care providers in conjunction with orthopedic surgeon Chris Peterson, DO 2003.</p>','Speaking Engagements','Dr. Penrose has been in the Olympia/Lacey community since 2001 and has established solid relationships with local physicians.  She has co-lectured with surgeons on shoulder, ankle, and knee rehabilitation.  ','publish','open','open','','speaking-engagements','','','2017-01-25 00:25:07','2017-01-25 00:25:07','',0,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/?p=399',0,'post','',0),(401,4,'2017-01-21 22:00:02','2017-01-21 22:00:02','','_MG_8084 (2)','','inherit','open','closed','','_mg_8084-2','','','2017-01-21 22:00:23','2017-01-21 22:00:23','',16,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/MG_8084-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(402,3,'2017-01-21 23:04:06','2017-01-21 23:04:06','','plank-1327256','','inherit','open','closed','','plank-1327256','','','2017-01-21 23:04:10','2017-01-21 23:04:10','',216,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/plank-1327256.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(403,3,'2017-01-21 23:07:39','2017-01-21 23:07:39','','core-training-1730330','','inherit','open','closed','','core-training-1730330','','','2017-01-21 23:07:39','2017-01-21 23:07:39','',216,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/core-training-1730330.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(404,3,'2017-01-21 23:13:49','2017-01-21 23:13:49','','shoes-1260816','','inherit','open','closed','','shoes-1260816','','','2017-01-21 23:17:23','2017-01-21 23:17:23','',216,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/shoes-1260816.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(405,3,'2017-01-21 23:34:09','2017-01-21 23:34:09','','lower-extremity-angle-