28:43','2017-01-22 01:28:43','',210,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Photo-Nov-08-8-55-49-AM.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(413,3,'2017-01-22 01:35:28','2017-01-22 01:35:28','','Photo Nov 08, 9 19 15 AM','','inherit','open','closed','','photo-nov-08-9-19-15-am','','','2017-01-22 01:37:20','2017-01-22 01:37:20','',11,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Photo-Nov-08-9-19-15-AM.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(418,3,'2016-10-22 04:20:50','2016-10-22 04:20:50','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-304\" src=\"http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Glowrun-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />\r\n\r\nPenrose &amp; Associates Physical Therapy sponsors local school races such as the Glow Run 5k as a fund raiser for Cornerstone Christian School.  It also sponsors The Friendship Run for the Westside Co-op Preschool.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-303 size-medium\" src=\"https://penrosept.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Friendshiprun-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"youth running sponsorship\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" />\r\n\r\nJennifer Penrose has donated her time as the cross country coach and assisted with the track team at Cornerstone Christian School.  Dr. Penrose enjoys teaching youth in correct running form, dynamic warm ups, and stretching.  She wants kids to just have fun running!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-302 size-medium\" src=\"https://penrosept.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/crosscounty-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"youth running cornerstone track\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" />','Youth Running','','publish','open','open','','youth-running','','','2017-02-10 20:42:46','2017-02-10 20:42:46','',0,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/?p=418',0,'post','',0),(419,4,'2016-12-28 04:32:38','2016-12-28 04:32:38','','Arthritis Success Story','','publish','closed','closed','','arthritis-success-story','','','2017-01-27 05:57:20','2017-01-27 05:57:20','',0,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/?post_type=case_study&#038;p=419',0,'case_study','',0),(420,3,'2016-11-24 02:30:32','2016-11-24 02:30:32','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-301\" src=\"http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Turkeytrot2-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.guerillarunning.com\" target=\"_blank\">Guerilla Running</a> does a wonderful job putting on a 4 mile Turkey Trot race on Thanksgiving morning in downtown Olympia, WA.  Penrose &amp; Associates is proud to sponsor this race and provide swag bags.  As part of the giving spirit of Guerilla Running a day volunteering at the Thurston County Food Bank is part of the culture in preparing for the Oly Trot Race.  They also encourage race participants to bring canned goods to the donation truck on Thanksgiving morning.  Guerilla Running also gives a monetary gift to the food bank from the race entry fees.  Guerilla Running has a spirit of giving and is a great running club that encourages running at all abilities.  Penrose Physical Therapy has been happy to sponsor and host running workshops for this club.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nVisit the Guerilla Running website to learn more about the Running Club and find more details about the annual Oly Trot race.','Olympia Turkey Trot 4 Mile Race','Guerilla Running does a wonderful job putting on a 4 mile Turkey Trot race on Thanksgiving morning in downtown Olympia, WA.  Penrose & Associates is proud to sponsor this race and provide swag bags. ','publish','open','open','','olympia-turkey-trot-4-mile-race','','','2017-02-13 15:05:31','2017-02-13 23:05:31','',0,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/?p=420',0,'post','',0),(422,4,'2017-01-22 04:35:20','2017-01-22 04:35:20','','woman-791541_960_720','','inherit','open','closed','','woman-791541_960_720','','','2017-01-22 04:36:47','2017-01-22 04:36:47','',419,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/woman-791541_960_720.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(424,3,'2016-12-10 05:04:53','2016-12-10 05:04:53','<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-306 size-medium\" src=\"https://penrosept.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/runnersworkshop1-e1484425457905-300x238.jpg\" alt=\"runner\'s workshops ball plank\" width=\"300\" height=\"238\" />\r\n\r\nJennifer Penrose enjoys working with the running population of all ages.  She has taken additional training in <a href=\"https://penrosept.com/runners-athletes/\">running and gait mechanics</a>.  She enjoys educating novice to experienced runner\'s on the latest evidence for exercises that keep runners injury free!  Runner\'s workshops are scheduled approximately once a quarter during the year.\r\n\r\nMost runner\'s workshops include instruction with hands on exercise handouts to take home.\r\n\r\n<strong>STRONG BODY  Runner\'s workshop\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nMost experts agree that running injuries can be from multiple factors: weakness, stiffness, the wrong shoe, inaccurate form, and training errors.  In order to reduce your risk you need to approach it from all angles: a strong body, good form, and the right shoe.\r\n\r\nIn the battle against injury, a runner\'s best armor is a strong body. Strong muscles, ligaments, and tendons guard against impact, improve form, and lead to a consistent gait.\r\n\r\n<strong>Why?</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>\"If muscles are weak, one footfall will not be like the rest,\" says Reed Ferber, Ph.D., director of the Running Injury Clinic at the University of Calgary. \"How your knee turns in, your hip drops, your foot pronates changes with each step. But with strength, these movements are the same each time, so your mind and body know what to expect.\"</li>\r\n 	<li>When a <strong>strong</strong> <strong>body runs, the brain tells the muscles to brace for impact</strong> before the foot hits the ground. The glutes and core contract to steady the pelvis and leg. The foot and ankle muscles are activated providing a solid foundation to land upon.</li>\r\n 	<li>However, if one stabilizer isn\'t strong enough or isn\'t recruited, other muscles get overworked, and the entire chain of movement is disrupted, says Eric Orton, a running coach featured in Born to Run.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Most runners lack strength in at least one muscle group, as well as in their neuromuscular pathways, the lines of communication between brain and body</strong>, says Jay Dicharry, M.P.T., the director of the REP biomechanics lab at Rebound Physical Therapy in Bend, Oregon, and author of <em>Anatomy for Runners</em>. Strong pathways help muscles fire more efficiently and in quick succession, which enables you to run with greater control and stability.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese exercises, adapted from Dicharry\'s and Orton\'s programs, strengthen running\'s key muscles and those neuromuscular pathways. You can do them as a full routine or insert them into your day perhaps while watching TV two or three times a week. If possible, do the moves barefoot.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-307 size-medium\" src=\"https://penrosept.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/runnersworkshop3-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"runner\'s workshops hip drive\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />','Runner\'s Workshops','Dr. Penrose enjoys teaching the running community how to prevent injuries with the STRONG body workshop.  \"Most runners lack strength in at least one muscle group, as well as in their neuromuscular pathways, the lines of communication between brain and body,\" says Jay Dicharry, M.P.T., the director of the REP biomechanics lab at Rebound Physical Therapy in Bend, Oregon, and author of Anatomy for Runners. ','publish','open','open','','runners-workshops','','','2017-02-10 20:36:41','2017-02-10 20:36:41','',0,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/?p=424',0,'post','',0),(425,4,'2017-01-22 04:39:50','2017-01-22 04:39:50','','old-friends-555527_960_720','','inherit','open','closed','','old-friends-555527_960_720','','','2017-01-22 04:39:50','2017-01-22 04:39:50','',419,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/old-friends-555527_960_720.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(427,3,'2017-01-26 05:14:58','2017-01-26 05:14:58','Dr. Penrose was the featured speaker at \"Eye on Health\" at Jubilee, an active retirement community in Lacey WA.  1 in 2 women and 1 in 4 men over the age of 50 will suffer from an osteoporosis fracture in their lifetime.  Osteoporosis affects 54 million Americans.  Osteoarthritis affects 27 million Americans.\r\n\r\nHere are the presentation slides.<img class=\"alignright wp-image-445 size-medium\" src=\"https://penrosept.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/workout-1931107_960_720-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"osteoporosis stability exercise equipment\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Osteoporosis-Osteoarthritis.pdf\">Osteoporosis &amp; Osteoarthritis</a> - click to download\r\n\r\nHere is the Osteoporosis handout that will help you put together a comprehensive exercise program to increase your bone density and improve your posture and core strength.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/exercise-recommendations-osteo.pdf\">Exercise Recommendations</a> - click to download\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Osteoporosis & Osteoarthritis Presentation at Jubilee','Dr. Penrose was the featured speaker at \"Eye on Health\" at Jubilee, an active retirement community in Lacey WA. She spoke about osteoporosis and osteoarthritis. Click to read more and download her presentation and the exercise handout.','publish','open','open','','osteoporosis-osteoarthritis-presentation','','','2017-03-02 12:01:05','2017-03-02 20:01:05','',0,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/?p=427',0,'post','',0),(428,3,'2017-01-22 05:27:24','2017-01-22 05:27:24','','exercise recommendations osteo','','inherit','open','closed','','exercise-recommendations-osteo','','','2017-01-22 05:27:24','2017-01-22 05:27:24','',427,'http://penrose1.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/exercise-recommendations-osteo.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(440,3,'2017-02-08 05:11:33','2017-02-08 05:11:33','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-447 size-full\" src=\"https://penrosept.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Doorpectstretch-e1486758514353.jpeg\" alt=\"door shoulders pec stretch\" width=\"529\" height=\"216\" />\r\n\r\nMost of the time the ache in our neck and shoulders is from overuse of those muscles.  Are you sitting up with good posture at your computer?  Do you carry your bag repeatedly on one side with considerable weight in it?  Do you use the \"arm rests\" on your chair to rest your arms and decrease the tension in your neck and shoulders?  Is the monitor at the right height so you are not leaning forward or bending your neck too far down?  All of those posture issues can create neck and shoulder pain.  Read more on the Thurston Talk site by clicking <a href=\"http://www.thurstontalk.com/2017/02/07/aching-pain-neck-shoulders/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','What to do about that aching pain in my neck and shoulders?','Most of the time the ache in our neck and shoulders is from overuse of those muscles.  Are you sitting up with good posture at your computer?  Do you carry your bag repeatedly on one side with considerable weight in it?  Do you use the \"arm rests\" on your chair to rest your arms and decrease the tension in your neck and shoulders?  Is the monitor at the right height so you are not leaning forward or bending your neck too far down?  All of those posture issues can create neck and shoulder pain.  ','publish','open','open','','aching-pain-neck-shoulders','','','2017-02-13 15:17:42','2017-02-13 23:17:42','',0,'https://penrosept.com/?p=440',0,'post','',0),(445,4,'2017-02-10 19:52:36','2017-02-10 19:52:36','','workout-1931107_960_720','','inherit','open','closed','','workout-1931107_960_720','','','2017-02-10 19:52:36','2017-02-10 19:52:36','',427,'https://penrosept.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/workout-1931107_960_720.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(44